40|$|It {{is known}} that the region V(s) of a simple polygon P, {{directly}} visible (illuminable) from an internal point s, is simply connected. Aronov et al. addpp 981 established that the region V_ 1 (s) of a simple polygon visible from an internal point s due to at most one <b>diffuse</b> <b>reflection</b> on the boundary of the polygon P, is also simply connected. In this paper we establish that the region V_ 2 (s), visible from s due to at most two <b>diffuse</b> <b>reflections</b> may be multiply connected; we demonstrate {{the construction of an}} n-sided simple polygon with a point s inside it so that and the region of P visible from s after at most two <b>diffuse</b> <b>reflections</b> is multiple connected. Comment: 10 pages, 3 figure...|$|R
